instruction:
Write a script named jsonl.sh. When run, it should create a JSONL file named data.jsonl with:
{"name": "Alice", "age": 30}
{"name": "Bob", "age": 25}
Then print the age of the second person.

Write a script named jsonl2.sh. When run, it should create a JSONL file named data.jsonl with:
{"name": "Alice", "age": 30}
{"name": "Bob", "age": 25}
Then print the CSV content with header name,age and rows in the same order (no index column).

Write a script named solve.sh or solve.py. When run, it should create a file obj.json with:
{"name":"alice","score":12}
Then print the value of 'score'.
